Grammy award-winning artist Wizkid has encouraged his fans not to feel depressed about current conditions. The father of three took to his Snapchat story to advise his followers in a series of posts. “Don’t waste your life with temporary situations. Live life,” he wrote.   People willing to pay me to pull stunts at parties- Pretty…     Omo Borty, Sydney Talker, others attend Abike Halima’s…     Umanu Elijah makes 2021 breakout film directors list   Continuing, the singer, who bagged five awards at African Entertainment Awards USA said: “I don’t wake up sad. I don’t wake up poor in life, in health, and in spirit. I don’t wake up with hate in my heart. Thank Jah for blessings every day.” - Advertisement - In another post, Wizkid opined that age isn’t a representation of how smart you are. “Age isn’t a representation of how smart you are. I know plenty of stupid grown people too.”